sub_title: Medewerker bemiddeling Oekraïense vluchtelingen bij UWV Haarlem
summary:
Currently based in Haarlem, Netherlands. Holder of Dutch residency and work permit. Registered with the Dutch Chamber of Commerce as a private entrepreneur (EMZ).

Since August 2022 working as a recruiter supporting Ukrainian refugees at the Dutch employment agency UWV in Haarlem 

Certified Russian-English interpreter and translator with 3+ years of experience in finance, marketing, law, IT.

Passionate ESL and FLE teacher with 5+ years of experience in both online and offline classrooms.

Offering highly personalized lessons for A0-C1 levels to young adults, as well as kids and teens. 
Proven results in test preparation for Cambridge exams and IELTS (both general and academic). 
Lessons are always tailored to specific needs and interests of my students to make it both enjoyable and effective. 
Whatever the topic and objective of the lesson, 80% is attributed to speaking practice, which is of paramount importance when it comes to language learning.
